Package: plot.pretty
Type: Package
Title: Prettier Plotting and Data Exploration for Continuous Data with Base R Made Easier 
Version: 0.1.0
Author: Edward Lavender
Maintainer: Edward Lavender <el72@st-andrews.ac.uk>
Description: This package provides a compilation of functions which make exploring data and creating publication-quality plots easier with base R. The package has been motivated by the requirements of continuous, ecological datasets (i.e. continuous responses and covariates), although some functions are designed to handle factors.
Imports: 
    dplyr, plyr, lubridate, 
    plotrix, scales, Hmisc,
    rlist, 
    stringi, stringr, maptools
Suggests:
    viridis,
    mgcv, 
    knitr, rmarkdown, 
    magrittr, pryr, devtools,
Depends: R (>= 3.5)
License: GPL-3
URL: http://github.com/edwardlavender/plot.pretty/ 
BugReports: http://github.com/edwardlavender/plot.pretty/issues
Encoding: UTF-8
LazyData: true
RoxygenNote: 7.0.1
VignetteBuilder: knitr
